article.headline: Southern 66, Jackson State 65
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) -- Chris Alexander scored 17 points and had three assists as Southern beat Jackson State 66-65 on Monday. Southern (10-10, 7-4 Southwestern Conference) led 33-25 at the half after Jackson hit just 8-of-27 from the field, or 30 percent. Jackson (9-14, 5-6) outscored the Jaguars 40-33 in the second half, hitting 13-of-32, or 41 percent, from the field. Southern shot 37 percent, or 19-of-51, in the game. Trayvean Scott had 14 points and three steals for Southern. Deon Saunders scored 11 and had eight rebounds and three assists. Peter Cipriano had nine rebounds, nine points and three assists. Darius Parker led Jackson with 14 points. Hilton Tompkins scored 10, Antonio Williams-Parker scored nine and Catraiva Givens had eight. Southern's Charlie White was ejected with 1:47 remaining in the first half for a flagrant technical foul.
